================================================================================
UNIFIED FLOPPY TOOL (UFT) - NOTICE
================================================================================

Copyright (C) 2024-2025 UFT Project
License: GPL-2.0-or-later

This software is an independent implementation of floppy disk preservation
and analysis algorithms. All code uses the UFT namespace (uft_*, UFT_*,
libflux_*, LIBFLUX_*).

================================================================================
ACKNOWLEDGMENTS
================================================================================

UFT was developed using publicly available specifications and documentation:

HARDWARE SPECIFICATIONS:
- Greaseweazle protocol documentation
- KryoFlux stream format specification
- SuperCard Pro (SCP) format specification
- HFE format specification

DISK FORMAT STANDARDS:
- ADF (Amiga), D64/G64 (Commodore), DSK (Amstrad/Spectrum)
- Apple II disk formats, Atari 8-bit/ST formats
- IBM PC sector formats, FAT12 filesystem

ENCODING STANDARDS:
- MFM/FM encoding (IBM standards)
- GCR encoding (Commodore/Apple specifications)
- Amiga MFM variant specifications

All implementations are based on public specifications and clean-room
reverse engineering of format structures.

================================================================================
